{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T03:40:56.912Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Underfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "overfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are the two primary failure modes in machine learning, directly tied to the bias-variance tradeoff. They represent opposite extremes of model complexity that both lead to poor generalization on unseen data."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Underfitting vs Overfitting — concept overview"}}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Core Comparison"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Underfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overfitting"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Definition"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model is too weak to capture underlying patterns"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model is too complex; captures noise as patterns"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training error"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Very low"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (near 0%)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Test error"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (similar to training)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Very high"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (much worse than training)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bias"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (systematic error)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Low"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (average prediction close to true value)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Low (consistent but wrong)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (sensitive to training data)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model complexity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Too simple"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Too complex"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Generalization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Poor (fails everywhere)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Poor (works only on training data)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Visual Mental Model: Fitting a Curve"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Imagine data following a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "quadratic pattern"}, {"type": "text", "text": " ("}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "y = x^{2}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "True Pattern:  ~~~~~ (curved)\n\nUnderfitting (Linear model):  ----- (straight line)\n                              Too simple; misses curve entirely\n\nOverfitting (10th-degree polynomial):  /\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\ (extreme wiggles)\n                                       Fits every noise point perfectly\n\nGood Fit (Quadratic model):  ~~~~~ (smooth curve)\n                             Captures true pattern"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Underfitting Deep Dive"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What happens"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Model fails to find enough patterns in training data"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Characteristics"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training error is high"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → model can't even fit training data well\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Test error is also high"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → equally bad on unseen data\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High bias"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → model makes oversimplified assumptions\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Low variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → predictions are stable across datasets (but consistently wrong)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Common causes"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n| Cause | Example |\n|-------|---------|\n| Too simple model | Linear regression on polynomial data |\n| Insufficient features | Missing key predictors (e.g., no \"location\" for house prices) |\n| Too much regularization | Strong L2 penalty forces coefficients to zero |\n| Training stopped early | Model hasn't learned patterns yet |"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Using linear regression ("}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "y = mx + b"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ") to predict house prices with non-linear relationships (e.g., price increases exponentially with size)."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How to fix"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- ✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Enhance features"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Add interaction effects, polynomial terms, seasonal terms\n- ✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Increase training data"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": More examples help capture patterns\n- ✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reduce regularization strength"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Overly strong regularization prevents learning\n- ✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use more complex model"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Switch from linear to polynomial/regional models"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Overfitting Deep Dive"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What happens"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Model learns excessive details and noise unique to training data"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Characteristics"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training error is very low"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → model memorizes training data\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Test error is very high"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → huge gap between training and validation performance\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Low bias"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → average prediction is accurate\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → predictions change dramatically with different training data"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Common causes"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n| Cause | Example |\n|-------|---------|\n| Too complex model | Decision tree with depth = number of samples |\n| Too many features | Including irrelevant noise variables |\n| Insufficient training data | Model memorizes small dataset |\n| Training too long | Neural network continues fitting noise |"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Two types of overfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n1. Both training and validation improve, then validation starts decreasing\n2. Both improve but with a wide gap between them"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": A decision tree creating unique rules for every training sample (including outliers) — works perfectly on training data but fails on new houses."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How to fix"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- ✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature reduction"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Remove excessive/irrelevant features\n- ✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Increase training data"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": More examples reduce sensitivity to noise\n- ✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Enhance regularization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Add L1/L2 penalties to limit coefficients\n- ✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adjust hyperparameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Reduce tree depth, increase k in k-NN\n- ✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Early stopping"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Halt when test error increases\n- ✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cross-validation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Detect instability across folds"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The U-Shaped Error Curve"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Error\n  ↑\n  │    Underfitting        Optimal        Overfitting\n  │       ●                   ●              ●\n  │      / \\                 / \\            /\n  │     /   \\               /   \\          /\n  │    /     \\             /     \\        /\n  │___/_______\\___________/_______\\______/___→ Model Complexity\n     Simple             Balanced        Complex\n    (High Bias)                      (High Variance)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Three scenarios"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bad on train + bad on validation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → Underfitting (too simple)\n2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Good on train + bad on validation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → Overfitting (too complex)\n3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Good on train + good on validation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → Ideal (sweet spot)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bias-Variance Connection"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Condition"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bias-Variance Relationship"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Underfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High bias, low variance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Low bias, high variance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Good generalization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Low bias, low variance"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": You can't minimize both simultaneously — increasing complexity reduces bias but increases variance."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Detection Methods"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "For overfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Monitor training vs. test error gap\n- Use cross-validation (large performance disparity across folds)\n- Track generalization error in deployment"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "For underfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Training and test errors both unsatisfactory\n- Generalization error close to training error\n- Model fails basic benchmarks"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-World Example: Spam Detection"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training Accuracy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Test Accuracy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Problem"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple (keyword match)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "60%"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "58%"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Underfitting — misses complex spam patterns"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Complex (deep neural net, no regularization)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "99%"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "65%"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Overfitting — memorizes training emails"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Balanced (random forest)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "92%"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "89%"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Good — learns general patterns"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Underfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = model too simple; high training error, high test error, high bias"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = model too complex; low training error, high test error, high variance"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Goal"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Find the sweet spot where both training and test errors are low"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Tradeoff"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Reducing underfitting (increasing complexity) increases overfitting risk"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fix underfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Add features, reduce regularization, use complex model"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fix overfitting"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Add data, regularization, feature reduction, early stopping"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The best models "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "generalize well, learn adequately, but not excessively"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Underfitting and overfitting are the two sides of the same problem — both fail to generalize because they're on opposite ends of the complexity spectrum. The art of ML is finding the balance."}]}]}}